---
import Section from "./Section.astro"
import ContentItem from "./ContentItem.astro"
import { experience, talks } from "../data/site"
---

<Section title="About" subtitle="Still falling, still learning.">
  <p data-reveal>
    For years, I've worked as a frontend engineer, building interfaces for
    large-scale projects. I've learned precision, structure, and how to make
    complex systems feel simple.
  </p>
  <p data-reveal>
    But somewhere along the way, I started craving something more personal —
    something that could reflect not just what I do, but why I do it.
  </p>
  <p data-reveal>This site is where that idea starts to take form.</p>
  <p data-reveal>
    It's not a portfolio in the traditional sense. It's a living space — a
    place to experiment, to connect dots between design and engineering, to
    explore the balance between logic and emotion.
  </p>
  <p data-reveal>
    I'm learning to move slower. To build with intention. To make things
    that last.
  </p>
  <p data-reveal>This space will grow with me — changing shape as I do.</p>

  <div class="flex flex-col gap-12 mt-8" data-reveal>
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
      <p class="text-xs font-medium tracking-widest text-neutral-400 uppercase dark:text-neutral-500">Work</p>
      <div>
        {experience.map((item) => (
          <ContentItem
            title={item.role}
            subtitle={item.company}
            period={item.period}
            description={item.description}
          />
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
      <p class="text-xs font-medium tracking-widest text-neutral-400 uppercase dark:text-neutral-500">Talks & Writings</p>
      <div>
        {talks.map((item) => (
          <ContentItem
            title={item.title}
            subtitle={item.type}
            period={item.year}
            description={item.description}
            href={item.href}
          />
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Section>
